OL,4,Csentenced for terror offences
OL,6,FAdil, 26, admitted two offences under
OL,7,Fthe Terrorism Act.JHe was handed an 18-
OL,8,Fmonth community order and 160 hours of
OL,9,Funpaid work for two terrorism offences
OL,10,Fat Westminster Magistrates' Court.JA
OL,11,FCPS spokesperson said: "Mohammed Adil
OL,12,Funderstood that in sharing the images
OL,13,Fhe did, it would arouse suspicion that
OL,14,Fhe was showing support for a terrorist
OL,15,Forganisation.J"The CPS will not
OL,16,Fhesitate to work with the IOPC and
OL,17,FPolice to prosecute these offences,
OL,18,Fregardless of the perpetrator's
OL,19,Fposition."
